\begin_layout Subsection
Vacuum components
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The instruments consists of three main regions.
 The entrance and acceleration region, the field free drift region, and
 the reflectron.
 Detectors are positioned both at the end of the flight tube (behind the
 reflectron) and at the 'beginning' of the flight tube, which is where ions
 are detected when the reflectron is in use.
\end_layout

